Site Coordination Group

The Lebanon Site Coordination Group is part of the Shelter & Collective Site Coordination Sector, part of the humanitarian contingency planning and response.

Activities

Level 1: Key activities under Crisis Preparedness and Planning

Activities Output
Supporting LRC and DRM in mapping potential formal and informal facilities that can be used to accommodate IDPs in worst case scenario. Carrying out joint assessments of identified formal and informal facilities in close coordination with LRC and DRM building on existing site assessment tools that is jointly reviewed to ensure site identification criteria have been considered. Have a list of sites including formal and informal sites that are assessed and verified from government entities that can be used for accommodating IDPs in worst. This list will be shared with DRM to be upload to their dashboard to ensure government and humanitarian counter parts have access to this information in case situations became more intense.
Mapping interest and capacities in Site Management and Site Coordination in close collaboration with LRC, OHCA, LHIF and LHDF using different tools including direct Kobo mapping tool and one-to-one verification exercise with LRC and Site Management partners to inform capacity building plan. Have a list of agencies, individuals, group of volunteers interested or/have the capacity in Site Management and Site Coordination to enroll them in a series of Capacity Building trainings on Humanitarian Response, Site management and Site Coordination, Protection Mainstreaming, DRR, first aid, etc.
Updating existing training materials in close collaboration with the LRC and DRR team to ensure Site Management and Site Coordination knowledge is reflected. Carrying out capacity building trainings and workshop in collaboration with Site Management partners and LRC based on jointly developed materials that can be used for training collective site/shelter management teams, NGOs, Volunteers managing informal sites and field operations room on emergency response. Have a unified training material endorsed by DRM and annexed to the National Response Plan that can be used in any Crisis Context to build national capacity. Have a list of NGOs, individuals, volunteers, community structures who are trained on Rapid Response, Site management and Site Coordination, Protection and others and who can be deployed based on needs to support with Site Management and Site Coordination
Developing a joint guidance document on Key Roles and Responsibilities for Site Management and Site Coordination in close coordination and collaboration with Site Management Partners, LRC and DRM. Have a Guiding Document that can be annexed to the National Response Plan and used in any crisis context.
